{
  "stem": "18575.7",
  "chunk_idx": 13,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "A-- Vietnam, they call them-- I forgot, there was a demeaning name-- gooks, [? kings, ?] whatever.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Well, then you can shoot them-- you can be against any people.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "To be aware of it-- unfortunately, people don't do it.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But that's the greatest danger, as Jews, we have experienced through centuries.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And you would think that the world has learned what happens.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But it doesn't.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Unfortunately, it doesn't.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Not only that, the anti-Semitism continues.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "There were no Jews in Poland.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "There's less than 5,000 Jews in Poland.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "But I was just there a year and a half, and there slogans, [? people ?] [? around ?] the world, the most anti-Semitic, horrible slogans, just like there were during Nazi time.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Same thing happens in former Yugoslavia-- you know, one religion on another.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "The thing in Ireland, the hatred-- [INAUDIBLE] there I once found a brochure on a plane flying from London to Leeds-- the same plane goes to Ireland-- that was taken word for word from Streicher anti-Semitic magazine, showing the pope with a big nose dripping.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "That was the Protestant thinks demeaning the-- I mean, horror.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I says, I hope that the world one day learned-- if they religious, that we are all children of God, and if they not, that life is sacred thing.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And there are not better human beings or more holy than others.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There are good and bad in all of us.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Fortunately, there are some good people.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There are the bad one, but there are good people.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Thank you.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "This is a photograph, a photo montage of a family from my father's side, part of the family.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "On the bottom, starting from left to right, is my uncle, youngest uncle, Fredek.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
